	     <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform"><span id="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=82561"><span id=" ">tzsjynx</span></a><br /><span id="notbold">313 posts<br /><span id="notbold">Score</span>: Good [4.00]</td><td valign=top class="mform" width="100%"><p>Just posting in case anyone doesn't understand what this does.<br/><br/>This procs (just like any other proc) and puts up a buff (which takes up one of your 15 slots.)&nbsp;&nbsp;The buff absorbs 5% of melee damage, increases base Damage mitigation (which yes does stack with AAs and does <u>not</u> work in inversed fashion like Haste, so theoretically you <u>could</u> get 100% Damage Mitigation but they'll never let that happen.)  <br/><br/>So this cuts off a % of incomming hits and the amount cut off by the damage is set against your 150 points on the buff.  That means say your taking 300 point hits, it will cut off 15 damage, and hit your 150 points with that 15.<br/><br/>This is quite crappy IMHO, for one reason and one reason only.  The buff takes up a slot on your 15 Buffs... Basically when tanking I can't even spare a slot for the Cleric's Vie line, which is like a MUCH better version of this.  The Mitigation does make a difference, but most of the time not noticably, and when you do need the mitigation, it will soak up 150 damage in 2 seconds making this relatively pointless.  <br/><br/>In the end, this proc just eats up 150 damage, thats all, its not even a good kind of 150 because you still are taking damage, it would be a better choice to just get 75point LT.</p>&nbsp;<br /><span class=sm>----------------------------</span><br />Warning - Attempting to patch together any coherent message from my posts may result in chronic headaches and/or intense vomitting.</td></tr>
